cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the generalization performance of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves transfer learning, which is a common technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve the performance of models. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dropout, which is a regularization technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the experiments involve the use of datasets commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research, further supporting the inclusion of this sub-category.
